      <data key="entity_type">concept</data>
      <data key="description">IoU threshold is a parameter used in NMS to determine when two boxes are considered overlapping, based on their intersection over union.&lt;SEP&gt;IoU Threshold is a parameter used in NMS to filter overlapping boxes.&lt;SEP&gt;IoU Threshold is a parameter used in object detection to measure the overlap between predicted and ground truth bounding boxes.</data>
      <data key="source_id">chunk-901133dd8268b83119819931e3df4d8a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fa4af6ae5dd3026673000e2a6ea963b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89fe41d130febd8488eedbf7569af292</data>
